channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Police ally of scandal-ridden Mayor Tiffany Henyard indicted on bankruptcy fraud charges
item.description: A top police officer and supporter of scandal-plagued Dolton, Illinois, Mayor Tiffany Henyard has been indicted by a federal grand jury in Chicago on bankruptcy fraud charges.

item.title: 'Squad' member Rep. Ilhan Omar wins Democratic primary in Minnesota
item.description: Democratic U.S. Rep. Ilhan Omar, one of the progressive House members known as the "Squad" and a sharp critic of how Israel has conducted the war in Gaza, has won her primary race in Minnesota.

item.title: Google Antitrust Ruling Is Government Picking Winners and Losers
item.description: Users choose Google because they like it, not because default agreements prevent them from switching to another search engine.

item.title: Parents Reward School Choice Candidates At Ballot Boxes Across The Country
item.description: Elected officials can and must implement school choice for the families of their state — or risk losing their political position.

item.title: 'Rubber-stamped': Key Dem hit over Biden-Harris support on border, inflation
item.description: Sen. Jacky Rosen is being targeted by the NRSC for her support of the Biden-Harris administration and their agenda.

item.title: Trump-backed Rep. Celeste Maloy wins Republican primary in Utah after recount, court case
item.description: U.S. Rep. Celeste Maloy narrowly won the Republican primary in Utah's 2nd Congressional District on Tuesday after the state Supreme Court rejected her challenger's lawsuit that asked justices to count a batch of ballots with late postmarks after Maloy defeated him in a recount by fewer than 200 votes.

item.title: Anti-Energy Kamala Harris Would Destroy My Blue State’s Economy
item.description: Has Harris abandoned her previous positions against fracking and natural gas, or does she maintain them? New Mexico residents would like to know.

item.title: Alabama Secretary Of State Finds 3,000 Potential Noncitizens Registered To Vote
item.description: Wes Allen is sending the registrations to the state's attorney general for 'further investigation and possible criminal prosecution.'

item.title: Trump push to dismantle Education Department met with enthusiasm in House GOP
item.description: Rep. Thomas Massie told Fox News Digital about his push to dismantle the Department of Education after it was a policy platform echoed by Trump.

item.title: Wisconsin GOP businessman Eric Hovde wins Senate primary, will face Democrat Tammy Baldwin
item.description: Wisconsin's U.S. Senate race was officially set in Tuesday's primary, while the power of former President Donald Trump's endorsement will be tested in a Republican congressional primary as Democrats decide on a candidate in a swing House district to take on a GOP incumbent.

item.title: Harris Swipes a Bad Idea from Trump
item.description: Exempting tip income from taxation is little more than political pandering, and ineffective pandering at that.

item.title: Behind Tim Walz’s ‘Hunter’ Facade Is A Plan To Take Your Guns
item.description: In just a few sentences, Gov. Tim Walz made false claims about assault weapons, background checks, CDC research, and reciprocal carry.

item.title: Former Minnesota resident unloads on Gov Walz after mother died 'of loneliness' during pandemic
item.description: A former Minnesota resident told Fox News Digital she moved out of the state due to Gov. Tim Walz's policies on coronavirus and rampant crime

item.title: Iran wants U.S. voters to think Trump assassination attempt was a hoax, cyber firm says
item.description: Iran was secretly behind efforts to paint the July assassination attempt against former President Donald Trump as a hoax, according to the cyber intelligence firm Recorded Future.

item.title: Progressives’ Revealing Inconsistency When Elections Don’t Go Their Way
item.description: When money from Jewish sources helps the Left, it’s good; when money from Jewish sources hurts the Left, it’s bad.

item.title: The New York Times Praises Democrats’ Immigration Policies For ‘Reshaping The Electorate’
item.description: 'The surge in naturalization efficiency isn't just about clearing backlogs; it's potentially reshaping the electorate ... .'

item.title: Trump campaign picks up the pace, eyes counter-programming during Democrats' convention
item.description: With Vice President Kamala Harris riding a wave heading into the Democratic National Convention, former President Trump and his campaign appear to be stepping up their efforts to blunt her momentum.

item.title: Trump-Musk conversation racks up historic-sized audience
item.description: Elon Musk and Donald Trump conducted a wide-ranging conversation on X on Monday evening. Yes, there were some glitches, but the exchange between the two drew a mammoth audience. Here are the numbers, as posted on X itself in the aftermath.

item.title: Kamala Harris Isn’t Running A Democrat Campaign. The Media Are Doing It For Her.
item.description: Kamala Harris has done no interviews or press conferences, and the media have ensured she doesn't really need to anyway.
